  "title": "Understanding HTML Structure",
  "lessonText": "HTML structure provides the foundation for all web content.",
  "data": {
    "content": "HTML documents are structured using a hierarchy of elements.\n\n*   **Elements:** Building blocks of HTML, defined by tags (e.g., `<p>`, `<h1>`).\n*   **Tags:** Keywords enclosed in angle brackets that define the start and end of an element.\n*   **Attributes:** Provide additional information about an element (e.g., `<a href=\"https://example.com\">`).\n*   **Nesting:** Elements can be nested within each other to create complex structures.\n*   **Document Structure:** A basic HTML document includes `<html>`, `<head>`, and `<body>` elements."
